<TITLE> International apparel tech fair opens </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 16 (bdnews24.com)A four-day international fair of garment and textile technology started in the capital on Thursday. Commerce minister Faruq Khan inaugurated the '10th Textech Bangladesh 2009 International Expo' at the Bangladesh-China Friendship Conference Centre. As many as 350 organisations are taking part in the fair from 17 countries. "International organisations rely on the economy of Bangladesh, that's why they have taken part in the fair," said Khan. He said local entrepreneurs will be able to increase production and export by using the technologies they are being acquainted with through the fair. He promised support from the government for the apparel sector and urged the foreign entrepreneurs to invest there. Fazlul Hoque, president of Bangladesh Knitwear Manufacturers and Exporters Association, said that there were potential to export apparels to Japan, Russia, South Africa, Brazil and many other countries. The fair is showcasing machinery for garments, construction and printing and packaging, general machinery, accessories, chemicals, yarn, power supply, air compressor, tools and cutter. The event is co-organised by Conference and Exhibition Management Service (CEMS) UK and CEMS Bangladesh. The fair, the biggest and the oldest of apparel technology, will remain open from 10:30am to 7:30pm every day. b
